# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
# |<----  Using a Maximum Of 50 Characters  ---->|

Subject:
<type>(<scope>): <description> (max 50 characters)
Body:
<insert detailed description of changes made in the commit> (wrap at 72 characters)
Footer:
<insert any additional information, such as references or issue numbers>

# <body>
# |<----   Try To Limit Each Line to a Maximum Of 72 Characters   ---->|

# <footer>

# --- Commit Message Format ---
# type: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, perf, test, build, ci, chore, revert
# scope: anything specifying place of the commit change (optional)
# subject: short summary of the change in present tense, not capitalized, no period
# body: detailed explanatory text, if necessary
# footer: reference issues that this commit closes, e.g. Closes #123, #456

# --- Example ---
# feat(auth): add login button to navbar
#
# Implement OAuth login flow with GitHub provider.
# Includes error handling and session persistence.
#
# Closes #42
